<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1794,2035]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,578,1866,1891]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Main morphological characters</emphasis>
(according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Foissner" box="[743,902,1866,1891]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" refString="Foissner, W. (1984) Taxonomie und Okologie einiger Ciliaten (Protozoa, Ciliophora) des Saprobiensystems. I: Genera Litonotus, Amphileptus, Opisthodon. Hydrobiologia, 119, 193 - 208. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / bf 00015210" type="journal article" year="1984">
Foissner 
<number box="[846,902,1867,1891]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Foissner" box="[959,1187,1866,1891]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" refString="Foissner, W., Berger, H., Blatterer, H. &amp; Kohmann, F. (1995) Taxonomische und okologische Revision der Ciliaten des Saprobiensystems - Band IV: Gymnostomatea, Loxodes, Suctoria. Informationsberichte des Bayerischen Landesamtes fur Wasserwirtschaft, 1 / 95, 1 - 540." type="journal article" year="1995">
Foissner 
<emphasis box="[1062,1120,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1127,1187,1866,1891]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Size 
<number box="[1264,1362,1866,1891]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="125.0" valueMax="150.0" valueMin="100.0">100–150</number>
<emphasis box="[1370,1386,1867,1890]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">×</emphasis>
<number pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="45.0" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="35.0">35– 55</number>
µm 
<emphasis box="[239,318,1903,1926]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">in vivo</emphasis>
. Body broadly drop-like, posteriorly broadly rounded. Two macronuclear nodules with a single micronucleus in between. Contractile vacuole ventral and subterminal. Extrusomes ovate, 
<number box="[1205,1219,1939,1963]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="3.0">3</number>
<emphasis box="[1230,1246,1939,1962]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">×</emphasis>
<number box="[1257,1292,1938,1963]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="1.5">1.5</number>
µm in size, scattered in cytoplasm of anterior body region and attached to anterior portion of oral bulge. Somatic ciliary pattern 
<taxonomicName box="[151,291,2011,2035]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Amphileptidae" genus="Amphileptus" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Pleurostomatida" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,291,2011,2035]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Amphileptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like; about 
<number box="[426,495,2010,2035]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="21.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="18.0">18–25</number>
right and 
<number box="[610,652,2010,2035]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
left kineties.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="508" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[360,616,152,176]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Amphileptidae" genus="Amphileptus" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Pleurostomatida" pageId="7" pageNumber="508" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="punctatus">
