a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,223,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Notes.</emphasis>
Records of 
<taxonomicName box="[412,553,224,248]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Amphileptidae" genus="Amphileptus" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Pleurostomatida" pageId="7" pageNumber="508" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis box="[412,553,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">A. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the territory of 
<collectingCountry box="[764,862,223,248]" name="Slovakia" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tirjakova" box="[877,1054,223,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508" refString="Tirjakova, E. (1998) Saprobiologicke hodnotenie vod Ziarskej kotliny na zaklade druhoveho spektra a abundancie nalevnikov (Ciliophora) [Saprobiologic water evaluation of Ziarska kotlina based on the species spectrum and abundance of ciliated protozoa (Ciliophora)]. Folia faunistica Slovaca, 3, 9 - 18. [in Slovak with English title translation and summary]" type="journal article" year="1998">Tirjaková 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tirjakova" box="[1066,1136,224,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508" refString="Tirjakova, E. (2003 a) Micro- and meiozoobenthos with focus on ciliates (Ciliophora) of the Gidra River basin. Acta Zoologica Universitatis Comenianae, 45, 29 - 40." type="journal article" year="2003" yearSuffix="a">2003a</bibRefCitation>
) are questioned due to the taxonomic difficulties and lack of illustrations or microphotographs. For further details, see Issue 
<quantity box="[1261,1305,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="7" pageNumber="508" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
‘Notes and discussion on the checklist’.
</paragraph>
